Text = “Teresa founded the Missionaries of Charity Links to an external site., a Roman Catholic Links to an external site. religious congregation Links to an external site. that had over 4,500 nuns Links to an external site. and was active in 133 countries in 2012. The congregation manages homes for people who are dying of HIV/AIDS Links to an external site., leprosy Links to an external site. and tuberculosis Links to an external site.. It also runs soup kitchens Links to an external site., dispensaries, mobile clinics, children's and family counselling programmers, as well as orphanages Links to an external site. and schools. Members take vows of chastity, poverty, and obedience Links to an external site., and also profess a fourth vow – to give "wholehearted free service to the poorest of the poor." (Source: Wikipedia)
